Proposed Solution:
We rotate z about c by angle θ = π/4 CCW. In complex form:
w = c + e^{iπ/4}(z - c).

Compute z - c:
z = (2 + √2) + i(-(3 + 3√2)),
c = 2 - 3i.
So z - c = (2+√2 - 2) + i(-(3+3√2) + 3) = √2 - 3√2 i = √2(1 - 3i).

